history.content: Oftentimes, there is no space in the classroom for waitlisted students to attend lecture, lab, and discussion as it creates room capacity constraints. As a waitlisted student you might get access to the course via bCourses.

I'm a BioE sophomore and I am wanting to do an EECS minor, thus i need to take 16A. I am 47 on the waitlist however. I have a backup class, but I have questions about the logistics of getting in off the waitlist. Should I be prepared to be on the waitlist once classes actually begin, and would i be able to attend lectures and lab and do assignments as a waitlisted student? This would be an awkward situation as I would have to do coursework for 16a and my backup class simultaneously. Any info and advice about the minor in general is much appreciated!
history.subject: EECS 16A waitlist confusion
